description: Three people died and two were injured after a building collapsed in Shahbaz village, Navi Mumbai. Believed to be illegally constructed, the building collapsed at 4am after cracks appeared. CM Eknath Shinde instructed local authorities to help the victims. An NDRF team found two deceased and reported multiple injuries and possible suffocation as causes of death.
title: 3 killed, 2 hurt as illegal structure collapses in Navi Mumbai

description: A cheating network was busted by the Uttar Pradesh STF during the CSIR NET exam at a Meerut university. Police filed a case against 23 individuals, including university employees and candidates. Electronic devices and documents were seized. Seven arrests were made, and investigations to find other involved individuals continue.
title: CSIR NET 'cheating': Cops register case against 23, 7 of them held

description: A controversy arose in Haridwar after a mosque and mazar were covered along the kanwar yatra route. Authorities claim no role, while locals express suspicion. An investigation led by police is ongoing. Cabinet minister Satpal Maharaj explained it was to prevent provocation, but critics contend it negatively impacts the BJP's image.
title: Uttarakhand cops probe covering of mosque on kanwar route

description: The Bombay High Court denied bail to a 21-year-old man accused of threatening to release photos and videos of his ex-girlfriend if she didn't continue their relationship. Justice Manish Pitale highlighted that such threats demonstrated a criminal intent.
title: No bail for man with 'criminal bent of mind' in blackmail case

description: A 13-year-old boy in Rewa, MP, allegedly raped and murdered his nine-year-old sister, with their mother and two elder sisters covering up the crime. The family falsely claimed a snakebite caused her death, but a police investigation revealed the truth. The juvenile, his mother, and two sisters have been arrested for their roles in the crime and attempted cover-up.
title: Boy rapes, kills sister; cops say mom, siblings hushed up crime

description: Pakistani military personnel and terrorists, part of BAT, attacked an Indian Army post at the LoC in poor weather conditions. The gunfight led to the death of one soldier and injury to another. This marks a pattern of infiltration attempts supported by the Pakistani Army. Security has been heightened in J&K, with additional BSF personnel deployed.
title: Gunfight after attack on Army post in J&K lasted for hours

description: The Indian government ordered the transfer of two BSF battalions from Odisha to the Jammu region to bolster security amid recent terror attacks. These units, comprising over 2,000 personnel, will support the existing defence line along the India-Pakistan border. This move follows several deadly incidents in districts including Rajouri, Poonch, and Kathua this year.
title: 2,000 BSF men rushed to Jammu from Odisha
India must strive to be $30 trillion economy by 2047: Govt paper

description: J&K police released sketches of three terrorists linked to the killing of four soldiers in Doda district on July 16 and announced a Rs 5 lakh reward for information leading to their capture. Security forces launched a search operation in Reasi after two armed men were spotted. Previous attacks in the district have left several security personnel wounded.
title: J&K police release sketches for 3 terrorists behind Doda attack

description: Rifleman Mohit Rathour was killed and a Major and three other soldiers were injured in an unprovoked attack by Pakistan's Border Action Team on an Indian post in Kupwara district, Kashmir. This incident, part of a pattern of infiltration attempts by Pakistani personnel, raises the monthly military toll in J&K to 12. Security measures have been tightened in response.
title: Army loses 12th soldier in July as Pakistan’s BAT attack post along LoC in J&K

description: A study by Brigham and Women's Hospital, published in Diabetes Care, analyzed sleep patterns of over 84,000 UK Biobank participants and found that irregular sleep increased the risk of developing Type 2 diabetes by 34%. The study followed individuals for 7.5 years, finding that consistent sleep patterns can help mitigate this risk.
title: Irregular sleep pattern ups risk of Type 2 diabetes, says study

description: The Karnataka High Court ordered authorities to enroll national-level swimmer Siri Srikanth in an MBBS course after she was unjustly denied admission for the 2022-23 session. Despite securing a high rank in sports quota exams, Srikanth was overlooked. The court found the selection of less-qualified candidates unjustified, stressing her national-level accomplishments.
title: Karnataka high court steps in, national-level swimmer gets MBBS seat

description: A 28-year-old speech therapist in Bengaluru was sentenced to 20 years in prison and fined Rs 75,000 for sexually assaulting a five-year-old girl during therapy sessions in June 2022. The abuse came to light when the girl revealed details to her mother after experiencing health issues.
title: Bengaluru woman gets 20 years' jail in Pocso case

description: In the Niti Aayog's 9th governing council meeting chaired by PM Modi, ten states and Union Territories were absent. The meeting emphasised the concept of 'Viksit Bharat' by 2047, focusing on federal-state collaboration, attracting FDI, ease of doing business, and governance. Notable absentees included Tamil Nadu, Karnataka, Kerala, and Delhi among others.
title: 10 out of 36 states, Union territories skip Niti Aayog meet

description: Bengaluru city railway station saw tensions rise when activists protested the alleged transportation of dog meat. However, food safety officials confirmed the 2,700kg shipment from Jaipur contained goat meat. The police filed three FIRs related to the incident, clarifying that the meat was a special breed of goat, not dog meat as suspected by activists.
title: 2,700kg dog meat seized at Bengaluru station? It's goat meat, say officials

description: Union minister Piyush Goyal stated that Sharad Pawar must apologize to Amit Shah for claiming the Supreme Court had "externed" Shah for misusing the law. Goyal argued that the UPA, which included Pawar, fabricated a baseless case against Shah due to Narendra Modi's rising popularity. BJP leaders defended Shah, asserting his innocence affirmed by the courts.
title: Day after his jibe at Amit Shah, BJP netas seek Sharad Pawar's apology

description: PM Modi urged states at the NITI Aayog meeting to create an investor-friendly environment and develop a vision for 2047. He emphasized good governance, law and order, infrastructure, and skilled workforce development. The session highlighted poverty eradication, agriculture productivity, and demographic management. Modi encouraged continuous evaluation and competition among states to enhance performance.
title: States must woo investors, Niti to draw up rating parameters: PM Modi

description: West Bengal CM Mamata Banerjee stormed out of a Niti Aayog meeting chaired by PM Modi, alleging her speaking time was cut short and her microphone was switched off. Finance Minister Nirmala Sitharaman and Niti Aayog CEO BVR Subrahmanyam refuted her claims, stating that Banerjee was allotted appropriate speaking time and that her mic was not turned off.
title: Mic muted, says Mamata Banerjee, walks out of Niti Aayog meet; govt refutes charge

description: In a letter to Speaker Om Birla, Congress MP Gaurav Gogoi raised concerns about the deteriorating parliamentary conduct, pointing out ministers' use of unparliamentary language and threatening remarks. He specifically cited incidents involving ministers Rajiv Ranjan Singh, Ravneet Singh Bittu, and MP Nishikant Dubey. Gogoi called for Birla's intervention to uphold the code of conduct in Parliament.
title: Gaurav Gogoi writes to Birla on mantris' 'threatening remarks' against opposition
PM Modi meets CMs of BJP-governed states, reviews key schemes

description: Maharashtra's deputy CM, Ajit Pawar, defended the Mukhyamantri Majhi Ladki Bahin Yojana, providing Rs 1,500 to eligible women, against opposition claims of populism. Critics, including Anil Deshmukh and Congress spokesperson Atul Londhe, viewed it as a voter wooing tactic. BJP spokesperson Girish Vyas highlighted its success in Madhya Pradesh. Analysts questioned its potential impact in Maharashtra's elections.
title: Mahayuti rallies behind 'ladki bahin yojana', oppn scoffs at freebies gambit

description: The Bombay High Court ordered 24x7 police protection for an interfaith couple from Mumbai who married despite family objections. The court directed Gujarat Police not to take coercive steps against the couple until their next hearing, ensuring their safety amid concerns they could be forcibly separated. The couple claimed the marriage was consensual and voluntary.
title: Give 24x7 protection to interfaith couple: Bombay high court to cops

description: The Rajasthan government considered raising the cow protection cess on alcohol from 20% to 25%. This would increase liquor prices and help fund subsidies for cattle feed in cow shelters from nine months to a full year. The government needs an additional Rs 225 crore annually for this extension, currently providing Rs 1,225 crore for fodder subsidies through existing taxes.
title: Rajasthan plans cow cess hike, booze to cost more

description: Nahoum & Sons, a historic Kolkata bakery, stopped selling chicken items due to the unavailability of a kosher butcher. The fourth-generation owner, Adam Nahoum, also decided to close the shop on Saturdays to observe the Jewish Sabbath. The bakery continues to offer popular items like fish pantheras and egg chops while observing Jewish holidays.
title: Non-kosher chicken items off menu as Kolkata eatery returns to Jewish roots

description: Kerala HC ruled that the Prohibition of Child Marriage Act, 2006, applies to all Indian citizens, regardless of religion, superseding Muslim personal law. The judgment came during a case involving a child marriage in Palakkad. The court emphasized that child marriage violates children's rights and stressed the importance of allowing children to mature before deciding on marriage.
title: Law against child marriage applies to all, faith no bar: High court

description: Lok Sabha Speaker Om Birla offered the INDIA bloc, excluding Trinamool Congress, a specific seating plan. Despite being part of the opposition, TMC negotiated separately for seats. The opposition is seeking more front-row seats to accommodate allies. The seating arrangement is crucial for coordination and management of the House, but finalization is still pending.
title: TMC in independent talks with Om Birla on Lok Sabha seating arrangement

description: Manu Bhaker made a statement of intent by storming into the 10m air pistol final before medal favourites in badminton and the men's hockey team got off to triumphant starts on a reasonably good opening day for India at the Olympic Games on Saturday.
title: India at Olympics: Bhaker, shuttlers shine on Day 1; hockey team wins too

description: Suryakumar Yadav equalled Virat Kohli's record of 16 Player of the Match (POTM) awards in T20 Internationals during India's 43-run victory over Sri Lanka in the first T20I of their 2024 tour. Yadav’s 58 off 26 balls helped India post 213/7. In reply, Sri Lanka managed 170, with Arshdeep Singh and Riyan Parag starring in the bowling department. Yadav's rapid accumulation of POTM awards highlights his impact and pivotal role in India's T20I squad.
title: In 56 fewer matches, SKY equals Kohli's record for...

description: A rocket barrage from Lebanon killed nine and wounded 34, including 17 critically, in the Golan Heights. Israel blamed Hezbollah for the attack and is preparing a response. An Israeli airstrike on southern Lebanon killed three Hezbollah members, escalating tension. The conflict between Israel and Hezbollah has intensified since the war in Gaza began after Hamas’ attack on October 7.
title: Rocket barrage from Lebanon kills 10 in Israel annexed Golan Heights

description: Suryakumar Yadav led from the front with a breathtaking half-century as India comfortably out-batted Sri Lanka by 43 runs in the opening T20 International to start the Gautam Gambhir era with a victory in Pallekele on Saturday. It was India skipper Suryakumar's 26-ball 58 and a 74-run opening blitzkrieg in just six overs between openers Yashasvi Jaiswal and Shubman Gill that took India to 213 for 7. Despite a fine batting effort from the Sri Lankans till the 15th over, the Indian bowlers did well enough to bowl out the home team for 170 in 19.2 overs.
title: 1st T20I: Surya-Gambhir regime starts with 43-run win

description: The Indian shooting contingent at the Paris Olympics is struggling with food and accommodation issues. The Athletes' Villages haven't catered to their culinary preferences, leading some to rely on a local South Asian restaurant or cook their own meals. Pistol coach Jaspal Rana has been cooking traditional dishes like Rajma-Chawal. Despite accommodation disappointments, the shooters remain focused on their goals, with Manu Bhaker advancing to the women's 10m air pistol finals. Their determination to end the medal drought is strong.
title: Indian shooters struggle with food and lodging at Olympics
1 student dead, 2 feared trapped inside flooded basement of coaching centre in Delhi

description: Jinder Mahal, now Raj Dhesi, left WWE after his contract expired, citing restlessness. Dhesi, a former WWE champion, is excited about his new independent wrestling career and numerous booking offers. Though WWE had almost retired him, he's ready for a fresh start with more opportunities.
title: Former WWE Star Jinder Mahal Opened up on his Exit

description: PM Narendra Modi considered visiting Ukraine in August to balance the Russia-Ukraine conflict and address concerns from the US and Europe about his recent trip to Russia. This would be Modi's first visit to Ukraine and comes amid tensions due to his meeting with President Vladimir Putin and following Zelenskyy's disapproval of Modi's embrace of the Russian leader.
title: To calm frayed nerves in US & Europe, PM Modi may visit Ukraine next month

description: Mehbooba Mufti asked home minister Amit Shah to form a joint committee of representatives from both sides of Jammu and Kashmir to address regional issues. She also called for reopening cross-LoC routes for trade and people-to-people contact and criticized the Central government for increased terror attacks in Jammu, urging Shah to focus on real issues instead of infiltrating local institutions.
title: 'Sit together twice a year and ... ': Mufti's advise to Amit Shah on bringing back PoK
Mamata walks out, Nitish skips: What was discussed at PM Modi-chaired Niti Aayog meeting

description: Manu Bhaker will have the opportunity to kickstart India’s medal tally at the Paris Olympics when she competes in the 10m air pistol finals on Sunday. Indian athletes will also be competing in archery, table tennis, and badminton on the second day of the Games.
title: Paris Olympics: India's full Day 2 schedule
'I will contest ...': Wickremesinghe announces candidacy for Sri Lanka's presidential polls

description: A $128,680 yacht owned by Robert Powell was attacked and sunk by a pod of killer whales during a trip from Portugal to Greece. The pod targeted critical parts of the vessel, causing it to sink despite efforts to deter them. Rescue arrived hours later, and the crew was evacuated safely.
title: Pod of killer whales sink $128K-yacht in Mediterranean

description: Sarabjot Singh couldn't believe his luck on the biggest day of his blossoming shooting career. On debut at the Olympic Games in Paris on Saturday, he huffed and puffed during the 10m air pistol qualification, stumbled, but got back on his feet like a boxer before the count of 10, throwing a punch back like he knows best -- with all 10s to post 100 in one of the six series.
title: What's an X that cost Sarabjot a place in the 10m air pistol final

description: India set a new record with a powerplay score of 74 runs against Sri Lanka in the 1st T20I at Pallekele International Cricket Stadium. Yashasvi Jaiswal scored 40 off 21 balls, and Shubman Gill added 34 off 16. The duo's aggressive batting led India to 51 runs in just four overs. Despite Sri Lanka's efforts, their bowlers struggled. Gill's dismissal at 74-1 marked India's highest powerplay score against Sri Lanka in T20Is. India reached 100-2 in 8.4 overs.
title: India etch new powerplay record in 1st T20I vs SL

description: Donald Trump at a Friday event hosted by the conservative Christian organization Turning Point Action urged the Christians to vote -- and then he said they would not have to do it again because 'We'll have it fixed so good, you're not gonna have to vote'. “You won’t have to do it anymore. Four more years, you know what, it will be fixed, it will be fine, you won’t have to vote anymore, my beautiful Christians” Trump said.
title: Trump tells Christians they won't have to vote after this: '...have it fixed'

description: External Affairs Minister S Jaishankar, at the 31st ASEAN Regional Forum in Vientiane, urged the global community to strongly combat terrorism, dismantle terror sanctuaries, and tackle cybercrime. He emphasized international cooperation for global security, ASEAN unity, and peaceful resolution of disputes, while also addressing Myanmar's issues and advocating for dialogue on the Ukraine conflict.
title: 'Be robust ...': India urges tough action on terror at ASEAN meet

description: Manu Bhaker qualified for the 10m women's air pistol final at the Olympic Games. She scored 580 in the qualifications, placing third and progressing to the final. Bhaker, who previously experienced disappointment in Tokyo, is now striving to secure an Olympic medal. Her strong performance brought redemption for Indian shooting after a slow start by other participants.
title: Who is Manu Bhaker? Pistol shooter enters final at Paris Olympics
Canada arrests 6 Indian-origin youths over extortions targetting South Asian businesses

description: The portrayal of villains in Bollywood has evolved from the exaggerated, larger-than-life characters of the 90s, like Amrish Puri's Mogambo, to today's nuanced and multi-dimensional antagonists. Modern villains, such as those played by John Abraham and Saif Ali Khan, reflect complex motivations and real-world issues, resonating more deeply with contemporary audiences.
title: A deep dive into Bollywood's iconic villains of the 90s

description: Former Indian opener Gautam Gambhir begins his first assignment as head coach of the Indian cricket team with a T20I series against Sri Lanka. His successful stint with Kolkata Knight Riders in the IPL has generated excitement. However, Sanjay Manjrekar downplays the coach's impact, citing India's World Cup victories led by different coaches. Manjrekar emphasizes player performance over coaching influence. Shubman Gill will be vice-captain for the T20I series under Suryakumar Yadav and ODIs under Rohit Sharma.
title: 'It’s really about...': Manjrekar slams hype around Gambhir

description: West Bengal CM Mamata Banerjee accused the Central government of discrimination after she was allegedly cut off during a Niti Aayog speech. Banerjee claimed only she, representing opposition-ruled states, was treated this way, while others got extensive time. Upon walking out, she emphasized the importance of state roles during crises and criticized the withholding of funds. Banerjee vowed not to attend future meetings.
title: 'Their CMs got 20 mins, I got ... ': Mamata sticks to 'discrimination' claim in Niti Aayog meet
Why '#CancelNetflix' is trending on X

description: The Congress in Chhattisgarh alleged political pressure on security forces in Bastar led to fake encounters and wrongful arrests, with misuse of muzzle-loading guns. Former CM Baghel criticized the current administration for mishandling the situation. The Congress plans protests against the Chhattisgarh Krishi Mandi Act amendment, which they claim benefits industrialists rather than local farmers.
title: Cong accuses Chhattisgarh govt of fake encounters, framing tribals

description: The 33rd Olympic Games began in Paris with a unique opening ceremony featuring athletes on boats along the Seine. Despite weather concerns, the event highlighted resilience and included a tribute to Hindi. Controversial acts, such as the recreation of 'The Last Supper' and the beheading of Marie Antoinette, drew criticism from viewers. This marks Paris's third time hosting the Olympics.
title: Outcry over 'disgusting & disrespectful' acts in Olympics ceremony
'Mamata jealous ...': Cong's Adhir Ranjan says CM's claims on Niti Aayog meet 'lies'

description: WWE's Liv Morgan has been a subject of public interest for her career and dating life. Known past relationships include Enzo Amore and rumored involvement with Tyler Bate. Recently, she's been linked to Bo Dallas.
title: Taking a look at the exes and rumored relationships of WWE Superstar, Liv Morgan
2 children among 8 dead after car falls into gorge in J&K's Anantnag
India, Laos unveil world's first stamp featuring Ram Lalla of Ayodhya

description: Rohit has had a stellar career, becoming only the second Indian captain after Mahendra Singh Dhoni to lead India to a T20 World Cup title. Under Rohit’s leadership, India won the T20 World Cup by defeating South Africa in a thrilling final last month. Having retired from T20 Internationals following India’s T20 World Cup victory, Rohit is now preparing to lead the Indian team in the upcoming three-match ODI series against Sri Lanka.
title: '7 ya 8': Rohit Sharma's bag-count confusion

description: Actor and BJP MP Kangana Ranaut, who does not shy away from making her views public, weighed in on the opening ceremony of the Paris Olympic on Saturday and criticised the performance as "hyper-sexualized, blasphemous" acts, which she said were a result of "Leftists hijacking the Olympics." The performance involved children apparently reimagining "The Last Supper."
title: 'Leftists hijacked Olympics': Kangana on Paris opening ceremony

description: At the East Asia Summit, India called for de-escalation in Gaza and expressed concern over attacks on commercial vessels in the Red Sea. External Affairs Minister S. Jaishankar highlighted the critical importance of sea lines of communication (SLOC) through the South China Sea for the Indo-Pacific development. India also reiterated its commitment to ASEAN and its collaborative efforts on various global issues.
title: India talks tough on South China Sea at East Asia Summit
More BJP-ruled states announce reservation to Agniveers in state jobs

description: Sharad Pawar highlighted the crucial roles of Jawaharlal Nehru and Sardar Vallabhbhai Patel in shaping modern India during a book release event. He praised Nehru's vision and Patel's administrative skills. Pawar also acknowledged Dr. B R Ambedkar's efforts in drafting the Constitution. Four books by Sheshrao Chavan were released at the event in Chhatrapati Sambhajinagar.
title: Nehru's vision of modern India was necessary: Sharad Pawar
Former Tamil Nadu BJP MP Master Mathan passes away

description: Akhilesh Yadav has vowed to scrap the Agnipath scheme within a day if his party comes to power, criticizing it as harmful. He argued for the old recruitment system. Meanwhile, Yogi Adityanath announced preferential treatment for retired Agniveers in police recruitment. The scheme, launched in 2022, recruits youths on a four-year term basis, offering 25 percent permanent positions later.
title: Will cancel Agnipath as soon as we come to power, says Akhilesh

description: Countries are often given unique nicknames based on their history, geography, or culture. Examples include Japan as 'Land of the Rising Sun' and Canada as 'The Great White North.' These nicknames provide insights into each nation's unique identity and background.
title: Discover how do countries get their nicknames: Check the list
'Insulted only oppn face present': Mamata walks out of Niti Aayog meet
Report claims 5 cr vote discrepancy: Congress
Vistara to offer 20 mins free wifi on its international flights, first Indian carrier to do so

description: Ranveer Singh is set to star in Aditya Dhar's next film, featuring a star-studded cast including Sanjay Dutt, R. Madhavan, Akshaye Khanna, and Arjun Rampal. Backed by Jio Studios and B62 Studios, the film promises an extraordinary cinematic experience. Meanwhile, Don 3 has been postponed to next year.
title: Ranveer confirms Dhar's next will be a 'cinematic experience'
'She was a bum': Trump attacks Harris, complains about Biden's exit in first appearance without ear bandage

description: Tamil Nadu chief minister Stalin on Saturday offered justification for not turning up to the Niti Aayog meet convened by Prime Minister Narendra Modi. The DMK supremo riding on a success from the recently concluded Lok Sabha elections, said he was "compelled" to seek justice due to the “discriminatory attitude” towards Tamil Nadu reflected in the budget.
title: 'Attitude towards TN': CM Stalin on skipping Niti Aayog meeting
Watch: Sunita Williams & other astronauts hold Summer Olympics in space

description: Team India's new head coach, Gautam Gambhir, begins his tenure with a tour of Sri Lanka, replacing former coach Rahul Dravid. Dravid expressed his best wishes and shared his experiences with Gambhir in an emotional audio message. The series against Sri Lanka includes three T20Is and three ODIs, with Shubman Gill as vice-captain.
title: 'Passing on the baton': Dravid's heartfelt message to Gambhir

description: Foxconn aimed to expand its Indian operations, initiating iPad assembly at their Tamil Nadu facility by late 2025. This follows Apple's strategy to diversify its supply chain away from China. The move aligns with India's PLI scheme and involves significant investments, including a new factory and mega iPhone production facility near Bengaluru.
title: Foxconn to expand its product manufacturing ops for Apple in India

description: After a faulty CrowdStrike update caused widespread system crashes, Microsoft is reviewing its security architecture. They are considering limiting kernel-level access to improve system resilience and exploring alternatives like VBS enclaves and Azure Attestation.
title: CrowdStrike outage: Microsoft wants to keep away the access from these cos
Karachi, Dhaka among worst, which are the most risky cities for tourists?

description: Harshad Patankar, recently released from Nashik Road central jail, was rearrested after holding a procession that violated police prohibitory orders. He was detained for an old attempt to murder case.
title: Gangster’s celebratory procession post release lands him back in jail

description: Central Railway fined its housekeeping contractor Rs 5 lakh after discovering 91 dead rats in the motormen's lobby at CSMT. Staff had to relocate due to the stench and protested against poor cleanliness. CR assured improved cleaning measures.
title: Contractor to pay Rs 5 lakh after 91 dead rats found at CSMT
True love: Family conducts 'bali' ritual for pet dog Emi in Kerala

description: A pioneering AI-based study in India identified microorganisms, genes, and bacterial pathways, increasing preterm birth risks. Researchers analyzed global data from 3,757 women, discovering bacteria linked to early births. A developing software and kit could assist in pinpointing infection-causing microbes, potentially reducing India's high preterm birth rates. The study aims to improve maternal and infant health outcomes.
title: With AI, Indian doctors solve mystery of premature births
PM Modi may visit Ukraine in August, first since war started

description: Ravi Shastri has backed newly-appointed T20I captain Suryakumar Yadav as Team India prepares for its tour of Sri Lanka. Shastri expressed confidence in Suryakumar's potential to excel as India's T20I captain and emphasized the importance of quickly understanding and managing India's diverse bowling options to ensure success in his new role.
title: 'He will have to learn...': Shastri's advice for T20I captain Suryakumar

description: Maharashtra state cyber cell arrested a Juhu resident, Ravi Kant, for posing as NCP MP Praful Patel to contact Qatar's royal family for business deals. Using Patel's photo, Kant sought assistance for business opportunities. The investigation is ongoing to determine any extortion motives.
title: Man poses as MP Praful Patel to contact Qatar's Royal family
Watch: Plane crashes in yard of Utah home with family inside
3 Army jawans injured as troops clash with terrorists in J&K's Kupwara

description: Abhishek, the suspect in the fatal stabbing of 24-year-old Kriti Kumari in Koramangala, has been apprehended. CCTV footage showed the horrific attack. Police are still investigating the exact motive. Abhishek will face a local court soon.
title: Bengaluru PG girl murder suspect held from Madhya Pradesh

description: S Samuel Raj, a 23-year-old cricketer from Chennai, jumped to his death from Kathipara flyover, reportedly upset over not being selected for the Tamil Nadu Premier League (TNPL). He was declared dead upon arrival at Chromepet Government Hospital. Police investigations revealed his friends suspected disappointment over TNPL selection was the cause. No suicide note or last-minute messages were discovered. His body was handed over to his father postmortem. Assistance for those facing suicidal thoughts is available through Tamil Nadu's health helpline and Sneha's suicide prevention helpline.
title: 'Upset over not getting to play' cricketer jumps to death

description: Fresh from his match-winning exploits to help India win the T20 World Cup last month and a break from the tour of Zimbabwe after that, Hardik will be keen to return to the field in Sri Lanka. However, he won't be the vice-captain of the side, like he was during the T20 World Cup.
title: Is that Hardik Pandya or Anil Kumble?

description: Ismael ‘El Mayo’ Zambada, co-founder of the Sinaloa Cartel, and his ally Joaquín Guzmán López were arrested in El Paso, Texas, in a dramatic capture involving deception. Zambada, a key cartel figure, faces multiple drug-related charges. His arrest marks a significant blow to organised crime and may lead to internal conflicts within the cartel.
title: How US tricked and captured infamous Mexican drug lord 'El Mayo'

description: It started from the Austerlitz bridge beside the Jardin des Plantes and made its way around the two islands in the centre of the city (the Île Saint Louis and the Île de la Cité) before passing under several bridges and gateways. Greece, the hosts of the first Olympic Games, started it off followed by the refugee team under International Olympic Committee’s (IOC) flag.
title: City of love gets Olympics underway with grand ceremony

description: In Navi Mumbai's Shahbaz village, a three-storey building collapsed on Saturday morning. Many were believed to be trapped. Police, fire brigade, and NDRF were actively engaged in rescue efforts. More details awaited.
title: 3-storey building collapses in Navi Mumbai, several feared trapped

description: Indian cricket management under new head coach Gautam Gambhir is focusing on Shubman Gill as the potential captain for all formats. Gill has been elevated to vice-captaincy for both ODI and T20I teams, and is expected to act as deputy to Rohit Sharma in the upcoming Test series against Bangladesh in September.
title: Is Gill earmarked as future all-format captain of Team India?
'I’ve got nothing against cats': How JD Vance defended 'childless cat ladies' remark
'Diluting quality of training': Tharoor on Agniveer scheme
Paris Olympics 2024: Google Doodle celebrates skateboarding

description: Former Sri Lanka batter Russel Arnold has praised Gautam Gambhir's appointment as Team India's head coach, predicting a fresh energy and preventance of complacency among players. Gambhir, who replaced Rahul Dravid, will make his debut in the upcoming white-ball series against Sri Lanka, highlighting his managerial prowess and ability to achieve results.
title: 'Players will be shaken up': Ex-cricketer on impact of Gambhir
Kamala Harris files nomination for US presidential elections

description: The Karnataka cabinet approved renaming Ramanagara district to 'Bengaluru South' to enhance its brand value and infrastructure. Initiated by deputy CM DK Shivakumar, the decision faced opposition from HD Kumaraswamy, who vowed to reverse it.
title: Karnataka cabinet nod to rename Ramanagara district 'Bengaluru South'

description: Team India captain Suryakumar Yadav replied to Gautam Gambhir's statement about not fully utilizing his potential during their time at Kolkata Knight Riders. Suryakumar humorously suggested that his full potential could now be utilized. Gambhir regrets that team combinations did not allow Suryakumar to be placed at the No. 3 spot at KKR, a decision he now regrets.
title: 'Toh abhi kar lenge pura...': Suryakumar on Gambhir's old 'regret'

description: Donald Trump and Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu met at Mar-a-Lago to restore their relationship after three years. Trump's support for Israel was reiterated amidst the Gaza conflict. Netanyahu discussed a possible ceasefire and US relations. Both leaders aimed to present strong leadership and diplomatic prowess.
title: Trump meets Netanyahu, attacks Harris over Gaza issue: Key points
